{
  "texts": [
    "Table 5 shows the set-up configurations that were used in this work for YOLOv4 layers.",
    "In this work, different experiments were conducted to select the suitable input image size for the network, so the experiments were done No of filters ( 18), (21) for two input sizes (416 9 416) and (640 9 640).",
    "Moreover, the model performance was evaluated by two different scenarios; the first one was to detect the existence of the masses regardless of their type (benign/malignant), while the other one was designed to detect the benign masses and malignant masses separately.",
    "Accordingly, the number of classes in some experiments was 1 class, and in other experiments was 2.",
    "This consequently affects the number of filters to be 18 with the 1 class detection and 21 with the 2 classes detection based on the equation mentioned in [10]."
  ]
}